title: For Sale:  Franchi SPAS-12
postcontent:
This shotgun is in great shape and works flawlessly. It's one of the few that can be switched between semi automatic and pump action. I may be interested in a trade let me know what you have. Mostly interested in remington 700's.

The Franchi SPAS-12 was a semi-automatic, 12-gauge shotgun noted for its variable-mode firing method in which the weapon could be fired via a gas-operated, semi-automatic mode (featuring self-loading) or a manually-actuated, pump-action / slide-action system. The SPAS-12 could, therefore, fire up to four rounds per second in the former mode, its dual-mode system managed by way of a two-position selector switch near the foregrip. The SPAS-12 was specifically designed as a combat shotgun and anti-riot measure but eventually marketed as a sporting system to civilians. Production of the series - handled by Luigi Franchi Development of Brescia, Italy (Franchi S.p.A), known for good quality shotguns - ran from 1979 to 2000 to which global operators became Austria, Bangladesh, Indonesia, Malaysia and the United States. The Franchi firm was eventually sold to SOCIMI of Milan, which filed for bankruptcy in 1993, leaving Franchi to come under the experienced leadership of the famed Beretta concern. its imposing external characteristics made it a popular featured firearm in Hollywood films such as "Terminator", "3,000 Miles to Graceland", "Underworld" and "Jurassic Park".

Century Arms – WASR 10/63 (AK-47)

For trade is a Romanian AK.  I bought this gun about a year ago at Fleet Farm.  I’ve put about 300-500 rounds thru it.  It has been cleaned after every range trip.  The gun has been trouble free to operate.  I haven’t had a failure to feed or fire with any type of ammo (I’ve used Tula, Wolf, and Herters in hollow point, FMJ, and soft point.  It eats them all). This WASR does not appear to have the canted sight issue that some are notorious for having.  The following are included with this rifle:

•	Tapco folding stock
•	LULA Mag Loader
•	Cleaning Kit
•	Tapco standard handguard (rail on top has been removed to see sights better).  Bottom rail is still intact under the protective cover.  
•	Original furniture
•	Tapco RAZR muzzle device
•	Cleaning rod
•	Sight adjustment tool
•	Krebs Peep type rear sight
•	Original rear sight
•	5- 30 round steel magazines
•	Quick release scope mount
•	1200 rounds of ammo (a mix of Wolf, Herters, and Tula) (not pictured)

•	The case shown in the pictures is not included, so you would have to bring your own case when making a trade.  

It’s been a really fun gun to shoot.  I don’t have any trouble hitting a paper plate at 100 yards, but it’s definitely not a sniper rifle.  It’s possible that the gun is more accurate, but my problem is that my eyes aren’t very good; I have problems with viewing the sights; and I’m not all that interested in putting a scope on it because it seems too bulky for me.  That’s my main reason for wanting to trade this for something else.  

I’d like to trade this for a large bore AR upper and hopefully some ammo to get me started.  I’m looking for an upper in either 450 bushmaster or 300 blackout.  I’d also consider a 1911 pistol.  A straight up trade would be preferred, but if you have a really good upper, I may consider adding cash.  I will want to see a valid permit to purchase or permit to carry as a precaution to myself.  I will not ask to make a copy of anything though unless it’s something you want to do.  

I live in Clear Lake, MN.  I’m willing to meet someone as long as the distance is within reason.

Please email if interested.  I don’t leave my phone number on sites like this, so leave your number in your message and I’ll call you back if you’d like to talk by phone.
